author: Guillermo Mario Narvaja
commit_message:
Support for env var substitutions (#168)

* Substitute envs feature

Optional parameter for Env object to allow recursive variable
substitutions.

Example:

```python

env = Env(substitute_envs=True)
assert env.str("PG_URL") == "postgres://gnarvaja:secret@localhost"
```

* Additional test for composite types and fix for dict parsing (and new
test for it)

* Fix lint errors.

* Rename substitute-envs to much better name expand-vars

Escaping support.

Recursion test.

* Fix README and variable name change.

* Deprecate variable proxying

* Remove allow_proxy

We can just remove proxying in next major bump

* Update changelog

* Update changelog

* Fix flake and mypy errors

Co-authored-by: Steven Loria <sloria1@gmail.com>
